Voice Assistant
This Voice Assistant is a Python program that utilizes speech recognition and text-to-speech capabilities to understand voice commands and provide responses accordingly. The Voice Assistant is built using the following Python libraries:
     speech_recognition: For recognizing speech from the microphone input.
     pyttsx3: For text-to-speech synthesis to provide responses.
     pywhatkit: For playing songs on YouTube based on user input.
     datetime: For displaying the current time.
     wikipedia: For fetching information from Wikipedia.
     pyjokes: For generating random jokes.
     webbrowser: For opening web URLs.
Installation
     Make sure you have Python installed on your system. You can download it from the official website: https://www.python.org/downloads/
Install the required Python libraries using pip:
**************pip install SpeechRecognition pyttsx3 pywhatkit wikipedia pyjokes*************
Usage
 Open a text editor or an Integrated Development Environment (IDE) of your choice and paste the provided code into a new Python file (e.g., voice_assistant.py).
Save the file and run the Python script.
The Voice Assistant will start listening for voice commands and respond accordingly.
Supported Commands:
  The Voice Assistant currently supports the following commands:

  play: Plays a song on YouTube. Example: "Play Shape of You."

  time: Provides the current time. Example: "What's the time now?"

  show me the Nptel exams in july 2023: Opens a link to the Nptel exams timetable for July 2023.

  who the heck is: Searches Wikipedia for information about a person. Example: "Who the heck is Albert Einstein?"

  joke: Tells a random joke.

  hello: Greets the user.

  how are you doing: Responds to the user's well-being.

  bye: Exits the Voice Assistant.
For any other input not recognized by the above commands, the Voice Assistant will perform a Google search and provide the user with search results.
Important Note
    Make sure to have a working microphone connected to your system for the speech recognition to function correctly.
    The accuracy of voice recognition may vary depending on the ambient noise and microphone quality.
    The Voice Assistant relies on an internet connection to perform Google searches, fetch Wikipedia information, and play songs on YouTube.
